@joaopalma5 Could you share your `docker-compose` version?

I have suspision that stat `nvidia.com/gpu=all` error means the CDI name is arriving as a `DeviceMapping` on `HostConfig.Devices`, older docker-compose (< v2.30, before https://github.com/docker/compose/pull/12184) does this instead of routing CDI names to `DeviceRequests`.

PR https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/28495 fixes the `HostConfig.Devices` path to preserve CDI qualified names. Could you test with the patched binary?
